			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ok. The idea behind the change they wanted to make was to make situational damage against undead more in balance between warriors and paladins. The solution is simple really. Give the warrior an innate melee ability that is specific to undead/summoned creatures. Maybe something along the lines of a melee discipline that the warrior can spend AA points into that allows some sort of high damage blow that gives him an edge when near death. Lets say the warrior is at 30% health, and the mob is at 30-40%, the warrior could trigger this discipline to offer a chance to kill the mob with the next 1 or 2 blows. I'm not sure how well this would go over, but the idea is this, to bring 2 classes into better balance, IMPROVE the impaired class, don't IMPAIR the other just because he has an edge the other doesn't. Just my 2cp :)
				</font>
			</td>

